rComments: Attendance is not really mandatory. He does randomly call on students to answer questions.
Teaches directly from the book. Attendance is optional if you read. It was his first time teaching the class so I'm sure his ability will improve. Overall a very nice guy.

It is clear that Dr. Henderson is new to teaching ChBE 221.  His examples in class consist of simply working out the book example problems line for line as done in the textbook.  Often times, he struggles to answer questions that deviate from what can be found in the textbook's working of the examples.  Surely with more experience he will improve

Very calm and happy professor. Class is somewhat difficult but helped by willingness to help with any issues. Emails can be terse, but don't take it as him being upset, he just writes that way. Attendance is pseudo-mandatory, in that he checks occasionally and is factored into an overall "participation" factor of the grade.
